<title>USA: Equifax set to buy Kroll Associates - WSJ.</title>
<headline>Equifax set to buy Kroll Associates - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Equifax was expected to announce plans for its insurance services group to buy New York-based Kroll Associates, which provides detective work to corporate clients, on Tuesday, the Wall Street Journal said in its electronic edition.</p>
<p>Terms were not immediately available, it said.</p>
<p>The acquisition was expected to be completed after Equifax spun off the unit into a free-standing company to be called Choicepoint, the paper said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>((New York newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
